😭😤😭😤😭😤If you’ve been to Nambantei in Tokyo, You will be so disappointed!  Food quality is comparable to a cheap chain restaurant like watami, failed the litmus test of not serving Highballs, and because they close early you would be rushed to finish... Vibe? What vibe.  They are plenty of better options near by really and stop spoiling the good name of Nambantei!

Nice place for lunch. Not too expensive, comfortable seating, and usually have space. 

Lunch set choices include a set of skewers/rice or just meat/rice. Although the skewers are not a lot (there's only 4, and you can add money for more), the salad and miso soup at the beginning helps fill you up a little.

reviews.text:
We came here for lunch on the recommendation of a friend.  

My wife had the gindara or cod fish set, while I had the beef sukiyaki.  Both were okay, though not exceptional.  We also ordered sticks of grilled pork and chicken wings filled with fish roe.  The sticks were better, though the pork was on the hard side.

Dessert was a piece of chilled vanilla mochi, which was actually quite good.

I guess the place is better at dinner time, with more people choosing grilled items.
